  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Therefore he lifted up his hand against them,.... A gesture used in swearing, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 14:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". So the Targum understands it here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"and he lifted up his hand with an oath, because of them:'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and so it is interpreted by Aben Ezra, Jarchi, Kimchi, and Ben Melech; and agrees with Numbers 14:28. The same gesture was used by the Heathens in swearing, as by Latinus (s). Or he lifted up his hand, in a way of judgment, to strike the blow; and which, when it lights on man with the indignation of his anger, falls heavy; see Isaiah 26:11. To overthrow them in the wilderness; as he did all the murmuring generation that came out of Egypt, all but Caleb and Joshua; all from twenty years and upwards, their carcasses fell in the wilderness; there they were wasted, consumed, and died, Numbers 14:32. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and so it is interpreted by Aben Ezra, Jarchi, Kimchi, and Ben Melech; and agrees with ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 14:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The same gesture was used by the Heathens in swearing, as by Latinus (s). Or he lifted up his hand, in a way of judgment, to strike the blow; and which, when it lights on man with the indignation of his anger, falls heavy; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 26:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". To overthrow them in the wilderness; as he did all the murmuring generation that came out of Egypt, all but Caleb and Joshua; all from twenty years and upwards, their carcasses fell in the wilderness; there they were wasted, consumed, and died, ",
            "children": []
