      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 32:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; the threat להפּיל, to make them fall down, fall away, after ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 14:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 14:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The threat of exile is founded upon the two great threatening chapters, ",
        "children": []
